{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/en/blog/2016-09-14-trinity-or-day-three/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"In the early morning of the 26th, I woke up ’cause of cold! I was dressed in all my clothes,\nsleeping in a sleeping bag in a fetal position…","fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-09-14-trinity-or-day-three/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"September 14, 2016","title":"Trinity or day three"},"html":"<p>In the early morning of the 26th, I woke up ’cause of cold! I was dressed in all my clothes,\nsleeping in a sleeping bag in a fetal position on a rug in a tent. And one I’m frozen! The tent was\nvery humid. AND VERY COLD! Somehow I forced myself to get out of the sleeping bag and ate. In the\nprocess, I warmed up a little. Starting to leave the tent, I took my shoes in my hands and was\nsurprised! It was wetter than I put it to dry. I dressed everything wet. Packed my stuff and went\nout hitchhiking. The hitchhiking was unsuccessful from the word ‘absolutely’. I had to walk along\nthe road to a stop, where I went from time to time to the Olzons. During this time I was traveling\nwith a military man, in a wagon, with a taxi driver, in a ‘bread truck’. Then I left the ‘bread\ntruck’ for the first time:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 4160px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/a3429/IMG_20160826_084320.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/f696c/IMG_20160826_084320.avif 1920w,\n/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/a5563/IMG_20160826_084320.avif 3840w,\n/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/8d91f/IMG_20160826_084320.avif 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/avif\"\n            /><source\n              srcset=\"/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/882b9/IMG_20160826_084320.webp 1920w,\n/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/93e07/IMG_20160826_084320.webp 3840w,\n/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/39c10/IMG_20160826_084320.webp 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/0f98f/IMG_20160826_084320.jpg 1920w,\n/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/e6b01/IMG_20160826_084320.jpg 3840w,\n/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/a3429/IMG_20160826_084320.jpg 4160w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/02f3f4b0cf2be28dd0f3fe26356cf3e5/a3429/IMG_20160826_084320.jpg\"\n            alt=\"IMG 20160826 084320\"\n            title=\"IMG 20160826 084320\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In Olzony the ‘bread truck’ stopped for the second time. The driver was Alexander. We rode with him\nto Elancy. He is from Angarsk. It was on the way in his car I understood that I was at Lake Baikal.\nNature has changed, frequent passes began, beautiful views from above to the valleys. The car was\naged and, when driving uphill, noticeably ‘fucked up’ from such loads. Interestingly, Sanya was\nfucked up too. He said that in these places for the first time in eight years, although he lives\nnearby. Just like me before this trip. He mentioned that he had finally found a tree for planting\nnear the house (there were different shapes, sizes, and colors). I hope that he still came there\nagain and took the desired tree with him. In Elancy, I changed my clothes behind a fence, finally\nchanged my socks (well I put on wet and leaky dry ones below), pet a cow, which got scared and\njerked away from me into a hole in the fence. The stop began unsuccessfully again. I had to go\nfurther on foot. And here again the ‘bread truck’. ‘God loves the Trinity, ” said the “old\nacquaintance”. He took me to the departure from Elancy, but, alas, it did not help. I had to walk\nfor several kilometers because of no “stoppability”. On the way, there were approximately the\nfollowing landscapes:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 4160px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/a3429/IMG_20160826_130042.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/f696c/IMG_20160826_130042.avif 1920w,\n/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/a5563/IMG_20160826_130042.avif 3840w,\n/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/8d91f/IMG_20160826_130042.avif 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/avif\"\n            /><source\n              srcset=\"/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/882b9/IMG_20160826_130042.webp 1920w,\n/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/93e07/IMG_20160826_130042.webp 3840w,\n/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/39c10/IMG_20160826_130042.webp 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/0f98f/IMG_20160826_130042.jpg 1920w,\n/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/e6b01/IMG_20160826_130042.jpg 3840w,\n/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/a3429/IMG_20160826_130042.jpg 4160w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/34738ba21bb167ed00288df638dc1fc7/a3429/IMG_20160826_130042.jpg\"\n            alt=\"IMG 20160826 130042\"\n            title=\"IMG 20160826 130042\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>More than an hour later, two cars stopped. There were 6 women of different ages in them. Not having\ntime to get into the first of the cars, I heard from the front seat: ‘And we have a man!’ They drove\nto Olkhon, and they dropped me off in Sakhyurt (which the locals call ‘MRS’), where the festival was\nheld. On the way there were a lot of chatting, we stopped near the monument with the eagle:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 4160px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/a3429/IMG_20160826_140235.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/f696c/IMG_20160826_140235.avif 1920w,\n/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/a5563/IMG_20160826_140235.avif 3840w,\n/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/8d91f/IMG_20160826_140235.avif 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/avif\"\n            /><source\n              srcset=\"/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/882b9/IMG_20160826_140235.webp 1920w,\n/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/93e07/IMG_20160826_140235.webp 3840w,\n/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/39c10/IMG_20160826_140235.webp 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/0f98f/IMG_20160826_140235.jpg 1920w,\n/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/e6b01/IMG_20160826_140235.jpg 3840w,\n/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/a3429/IMG_20160826_140235.jpg 4160w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/fdc4b3ea9b12db3b5b785251ccae1d0e/a3429/IMG_20160826_140235.jpg\"\n            alt=\"IMG 20160826 140235\"\n            title=\"IMG 20160826 140235\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 4160px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/a3429/IMG_20160826_140040.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/f696c/IMG_20160826_140040.avif 1920w,\n/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/a5563/IMG_20160826_140040.avif 3840w,\n/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/8d91f/IMG_20160826_140040.avif 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/avif\"\n            /><source\n              srcset=\"/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/882b9/IMG_20160826_140040.webp 1920w,\n/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/93e07/IMG_20160826_140040.webp 3840w,\n/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/39c10/IMG_20160826_140040.webp 4160w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/0f98f/IMG_20160826_140040.jpg 1920w,\n/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/e6b01/IMG_20160826_140040.jpg 3840w,\n/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/a3429/IMG_20160826_140040.jpg 4160w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 4160px) 100vw, 4160px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/7e23863600268e6df0e7b8bf58b5b616/a3429/IMG_20160826_140040.jpg\"\n            alt=\"IMG 20160826 140040\"\n            title=\"IMG 20160826 140040\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The road to such a popular place as Olkhon was unpleasantly surprised: a dirt road, very\nuncomfortable, dusty and bumpy.</p>\n<p>In MRS, I just climbed up from the highway and found myself at a recreation center, where there was\nno one at the entrance, although the entrance was paid. I went to the CSLT’s yurt. The clock was\nabout 15 o’clock. My first hitchhiking at ≈1300 km. took ≈2.5 days. It was great!</p>","id":"fb934d6d-a1b8-5337-bfe4-4ce438a1b7d2"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"🇺🇦 #nowar #noputin #nolukashenko #нетвойне #нетпутину #нетлукашенко ITFarrier"}}},"pageContext":{"langKey":"en","language":"en","next":{"fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2021-08-01-in-the-wake-of-the-onliner/"},"frontmatter":{"language":null,"title":"In the wake of the Onliner","type":"post"}},"previous":{"fields":{"langKey":"en","slug":"/en/blog/2016-09-13-silence-or-day-two/"},"frontmatter":{"language":null,"title":"Silence or day two","type":"post"}},"slug":"/en/blog/2016-09-14-trinity-or-day-three/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2674376943","357539041","4035578580"]}